***North Shapsugs, Great Shapsugs, Kuban Shapsugs (Шапсыгъэ шху) dialect
****[[Kfar Kama Adyghe dialect|Kfar Kama dialect]] (Кфар Камэм ишапсыгъэбзэ)
***Temirgoy-Shapsugs, Pseuşko accent (Кӏэмгуе-шапсыгъ)
***South Shapsugs, Small Shapsugs, Coastal Shapsugs, Black Sea Shapsugs (Шапсыгъэ-цӏыкӏу) dialect
***[[Hakuchi Adyghe dialect|Hakuchi dialect]] (ХьакӀуцубзэ, Къарацхаибзэ)
**[[Natukhai#Language|Natukhai dialect]] ({{lang-ady|Нэтӏхъуаджэбзэ}})
**[[Zhaney]] dialect
*The [[Kuban River]] dialects:
**[[Bzhedug Adyghe dialect|Bzhedug dialect]] ({{lang-ady|Бжъэдыгъубзэ}}): spoken by Circassians in the [[Republic of Adygea]] and the [[Biga, Çanakkale|Biga]] district of the city of [[Çanakkale]] in [[Turkey]]
**[[Temirgoy]] ({{lang-ady|КӀэмыгуябзэ, КӀэмгуибзэ}}): [[Literary language|literary]] standard of Adyghe. Also spoken by Circassians in the [[Republic of Adygea]]
**[[Abzakh Adyghe dialect|Abzakh dialect]] ({{lang-ady|Aбдзэхабзэ}}): spoken by Circassians in the village of [[Rehaniya]] in [[Israel]] and Circassians in Syria from the [[Golan Heights]]
**[[Mamkhegh]] dialect
**[[Yegeruqay]] dialect
**[[Hatuqwai]] dialect
**[[Mequash]] dialect

== Phonology ==
{{Main article|Adyghe phonology}}
Adyghe exhibits a large number of consonants: between 50 and 60 consonants in the various Adyghe dialects. All dialects possess a contrast between plain and labialized [[glottal stop]]s. A very unusual minimal contrast, and possibly unique to the [[Abzakh Adyghe dialect|Abzakh dialect]] of Adyghe, is a three-way contrast between plain, [[labialized]] and [[Palatalization (phonetics)|palatalized]] [[glottal stop]]s (although a palatalized glottal stop is also found in [[Hausa language|Hausa]]). The [[Black Sea]] dialect of Adyghe contains a very uncommon sound: a [[bidental consonant|bidental]] [[voiceless bidental fricative|fricative {{IPA|[h̪͆]}}]], which corresponds to the [[voiceless velar fricative]] {{IPA|[x]}} found in other varieties of Adyghe.

