# <b>Note: Adyghe has many consonants that appear in dialects other than those mentioned above or in the table, and has a complex system of consonant allophony. More information on those can be found at [[Adyghe phonology|Adyghe phonology]]. </b>

In contrast to its large consonant inventory, Adyghe has only three phonemic vowels in a [[vertical vowel system]].

