=== Labialised consonants ===

Гу [ɡʷ], Гъу [ʁʷ], Дзу [d͡zʷ], Ку [kʷ], Къу [qʷ], КIу [kʷʼ], ПIу [pʷʼ], ТIу [tʷʼ], Хъу [χʷ], Цу [t͡sʷ], Шъу [ʃʷ], ШIу [ʃʷʼ], Iу [ʔʷ].

In some dialects : Кхъу [q͡χʷ], Ху [xʷ], Чъу [t͡ɕʷ].

=== Writing system rules ===

* The letter {{angle bracket|ы}} {{IPA|[ə]}} is not written after a {{angle bracket|у}} {{IPA|[w]}}, {{angle bracket|й}} {{IPA|[j]}} or a labialised consonant. For example, : унэ {{IPA|[wəna]}} "house" instead of уынэ, илъэс {{IPA|[jəɬas]}} "year" instead of йылъэс, шӏу {{IPA|[ʃʷʼə]}} "well" instead of шӏуы, цумпэ {{IPA|[t͡sʷəmpa]}} "strawberry" instead of цуымпэ.
* In case the letter {{angle bracket|у}} is the first letter of a word or when is not related to any other consonant, it is pronounced as [wə] {{angle bracket|уы}}. For example, : унэ [wəna] "house" instead of уынэ, урыс [wərəs] "Russian" instead of уырыс, куу [kʷəwə] "deep" instead of кууы. When it's related to a consonant it becomes a vowel and pronounced as [əw]~[u] {{angle bracket|ыу}}. For example, : чэту [t͡ʃaːtəw] "cat" instead of чэтыу, бзу [bzəw] "bird" instead of бзыу, дуней [dəwnej] "world" instead of дыуней.
* In case a labialised consonant is followed by a vowel {{angle bracket|э}} [a], instead of the letter {{angle bracket|у}} there is a {{angle bracket|о}}. For example, : гъогу [ʁʷaɡʷ] "road" instead of гъуэгу, машӏо [maːʃʷʼa] "fire" instead of машӏуэ, шъо [ʃʷa] "you (plural)" instead of шъуэ.
* In case a labialised consonant is followed by a vowel {{angle bracket|а}} [aː] or {{angle bracket|и}} [i/əj], the labialised consonant letter is written fully. for example : цуакъэ [t͡sʷaːqa] "shoes", гуащэ [ɡʷaɕa] "princes", шъуи [ʃʷəj] "yours (plural).
* In case the letter {{angle bracket|о}} is the first letter of a word or when is not related to any other consonant, it is pronounced as [wa] {{angle bracket|уэ}}. For example : о [wa] "you" instead of уэ, орэд [warad] "song" instead of уэрэд, онтэгъу [wantaʁʷ] "heavy" instead of уэнтэгъу, зао [zaːwa] "war" instead of зауэ, ныо [nəwa] "old woman" instead of ныуэ.
* In case the letter {{angle bracket|е}} is the first letter of a word or when is not related to any other consonant, it is pronounced as [ja] {{angle bracket|йэ}}. For example, : еӏо [jaʔʷa] "he says" instead of йэӏо, еплъы [japɬə] "he sees" instead of йэплъы, мые [məja] "apple" instead of мыйэ, бае [baːja] "rich" instead of байэ, шъэжъые [ʂaʐəja] "knife" instead of шъэжъыйэ. When it's related to a consonant it becomes a vowel and pronounced as [aj]~[e] {{angle bracket|эй}}. For example, : делэ [dajla] "fool" instead of дэйлэ, къедж [qajd͡ʒ] "read" instead of къэйдж, непэ [najpa] "today" instead of нэйпэ.
* In case the letter {{angle bracket|и}} is the first letter of a word or when is not related to any other consonant, it is pronounced as [jə] {{angle bracket|йы}}. For example, : илъэс [jəɬas] "year" instead of йылъэс, иунэ [jəwəna] "his house" instead of йыуын, шӏои [ʃʷʼajə] "dirty" instead of шӏойы, дэи [dajə] "bad" instead of дэйы. When it's related to a consonant it becomes a vowel and pronounced as [əj]~[i] {{angle bracket|ый}}. For example, : сиӏ [səjʔ] "I have" instead of сыйӏ, уиунэ [wəjwəna] "your house" instead of уыйуынэ, къины [qəjnə] "hard" instead of къыйны.

=== Vowels ===
The vowels are written {{angle bracket|ы}} {{IPA|[ə]}}, {{angle bracket|э}} {{IPA|[a]}} and {{angle bracket|а}} {{IPA|[aː]}}.

Other letters represent diphthongs: {{angle bracket|я}} represents {{IPA|[jaː]}}, {{angle bracket|и}} {{IPA|[jə]}} or {{IPA|[əj]}}, {{angle bracket|о}} {{IPA|[wa]}} or {{IPA|[o]}}, {{angle bracket|у}} represent {{IPA|[u]}} or {{IPA|[w]}} or {{IPA|[wə]}} and {{angle bracket|е}} represents {{IPA|[aj]}} or {{IPA|[ja]}}.

== Writing systems ==
Modern Adyghe uses a [[Cyrillic alphabet|Cyrillic]] alphabet with the addition of the letter {{angle bracket|Ӏ}} ([[palochka]]). Previously, [[Arabic script|Arabic]] (before 1927) and [[Latinisation (USSR)|Latin]] (1927–38) [[alphabet]]s had been used.

