{{unreferenced|date=July 2013}}
'''''Pro Juventute''''' is a charitable foundation in [[Switzerland]] established in 1912. It is dedicated to supporting the rights and needs of Swiss children and youth.
Since 1913, the [[Swiss Post|Swiss post office]] has issued an annual [[charity stamp]] series to support the work of Pro Juventute.
Until the 1970s, the semi-official policy of institutionalizing [[Yenish people|Yenish]] parents and having their children adopted by more "normal" Swiss citizens was carried out by Pro Juventute on behalf of the Swiss government. The name of this program was ''[[Kinder der Landstrasse]]'' ("children of the road").
==External links== * [http://www.projuventute.ch/ Official website]. * [http://www.timbressuisses.ch/encapsulation.php?page=tpjuv The Pro Juventute stamps], on ''Timbressuisses.ch'' ; retrieved 19 April 2009.
